detail.title: [Community Spend Proposal] Airdrop Wave 1, to reward Quasar Testnet participants
detail.description:
# [Community Spend Proposal] Airdrop Wave 1, to reward Quasar Testnet participants
Authors: [Quasar](https://twitter.com/quasarfi)

## Proposal Overview:
We're putting forth a request for 10,245,750 QSR tokens from the community pool for the first wave of our airdrop series.

## Eligibility for the First Wave:
For this initial wave, we're looking at individuals who made at least three transactions on the Quasar Testnet up until March 10th, the day our testnet activities wrapped up. This criteria covers 2,157 addresses, each of which stands to receive an estimated 4750 $QSR. 

## Key Points:
- **First Wave Focus**: This wave is specifically for users who actively engaged with the Testnet, making at least three transactions (1x faucet and 2x vault deposits for example).
- **Token Allocation**: We're aiming to source 10,245,750 QSR tokens from the community pool for this wave.
- **Bonus Scheme**: Those choosing to stake their airdropped tokens will secure a bonus. However, moving these tokens to another address will nullify this bonus. Users that have also converted into mainnet users of Quasar will receive another bonus for their testnet participation.
- **Claiming Process**: Once the proposal secures approval, guidelines on how to claim tokens will be communicated through our official channels. A 30-day period will be allotted for claims. Unclaimed tokens will revert to the Community Pool. Claiming is scheduled to be enabled at the end of November. 
- **Upcoming Airdrops**: The second wave aims to reward participants of the legacy PRO Vaults, while the third wave is set to target users of the Concentrated Liquidity Vaults. Those will be separate governance proposals as well.

## Rationale:
- **Gratitude in Action**: This initiative is our way of thanking those who lent their voices and effort to our Testnet, offering invaluable feedback.
- **Increase Float, Staking % & LP**: More community holders means deeper liquidity for trading, higher security through staking and higher volume for our CL vaults to facilitate.
- **Expanding $QSR Community**: A broader holder base helps our decentralisation efforts, creates more aligned and valuable community feedback and is an important step in increasing $QSR role in the Quasar Platform.

## Procedure:
- Quasar Association multisig address receives the requested funds .(quasar1ed6ezqx9t4e9sfm6nfgulq3005umrh6hsqksnp)
- Once the contract is prepared, the association redirects the funds to the airdrop contract. Scheduled end of November.
- The airdrop process is initiated.

## Voting
- By voting **YES**, you agree to the changes above proposal suggests.
- By voting **NO**, you disagree to the changes above proposal suggests.
- By voting **ABSTAIN**, you express no opinion on the matter.
- A **NoWithVeto** vote indicates a proposal either (1) is deemed to be spam, i.e., irrelevant to Quasar, (2) disproportionately infringes on minority interests, or (3) violates or encourages violation of the rules of engagement as currently set out by Quasar governance

detail.title: [Signaling Proposal] for OSMO/ATOM A+ Vault Slippage Compensation
detail.description:
# [Signaling Proposal] for OSMO/ATOM A+ Vault Slippage Compensation
Authors: [Quasar](https://twitter.com/quasarfi)

# Summary
The OSMO/ATOM A+ vault has, in two instances, experienced unexpectedly high slippage during a rebalance, which affected underlying assets. Fixes have been implemented already & we have successfully done multiple swaps without issues since then. However, it’s crucial to note that no other vaults faced this issue. Despite no legal obligations, the Quasar Association would like to formally ask the community if it could compensate affected users.

## Details
The OSMO/ATOM A+ vault underwent anomalous slippage and price impact during two rebalances, which in the first case was 1k USD total. Another rebalance event resulted in a 6.5k USD slippage. As a response to these issues, steps were taken to counteract the problem. By utilizing robust proprietary routing mechanisms and a combination of TWAP and per-block fractional transactions, the vault can mitigate severe slippage and price impact, even on large, high six-figure rebalances.
Although the product is experimental and there’s no legal requirement, the Quasar Association has opted to reimburse users in ATOM. The total compensation, factoring in both events, is 7.5k USD, based on the difference when compared to a standard swap on Osmosis.
For those interested in reviewing the transaction details, you can find both transactions here:
* https://www.mintscan.io/osmosis/tx/F87ED8B2D4B93C18E172AC3B5FDBB0FD1C5B30B51B0C3261CB1EFAB43150A82E
* https://www.mintscan.io/osmosis/tx/ED61A26421FF65073FD1533F8A92ABD74FE48B1E33F819DAEA5AF7A6BC25007A?height=11594281

## Conclusion
We recognize the importance of addressing issues promptly and transparently. Our commitment is to continuously improve and ensure optimal performance for our users. 
Thank you for your patience and support.

## Voting

- By voting **NO**, you disagree to the changes above proposal suggests.

detail.title: Proposal to Increase Minimum Deposit for Proposals
detail.description:
# [Parameter change] Proposal to Increase Minimum Deposit for Proposals
Authors: [Quasar](https://twitter.com/quasarfi)

# Summary
This proposal suggests increasing the minimum deposit required for submitting governance proposals on Quasar chain from the current threshold of 2,000 QSR tokens to 20,000 QSR tokens. The purpose of this change is to mitigate spam proposals and ensure that proposals submitted to the network carry a more substantial commitment from the proposers. It is intended to enhance the overall quality of proposals and reduce the burden on the governance process caused by frivolous or insincere submissions.

## Motivation
In recent times, the network has experienced an increasing number of spam proposals with low deposit thresholds. These proposals often lack substance and consume valuable network resources, including validators' time and attention. This surge in low-quality proposals can hinder the governance process's effectiveness, making it challenging to prioritize and address genuinely important matters.

By raising the minimum deposit required to submit a proposal, we aim to achieve several important goals:
- **Deter Spam**: A higher deposit requirement will discourage proposers with insincere intentions from submitting frivolous or spam proposals, reducing the noise in the governance system.
- **Enhance Commitment**: Proposers will need to commit a more significant stake to submit a proposal, demonstrating a genuine interest in the network's improvement. This increased commitment aligns with the network's long-term success.
- **Prioritize Serious Proposals**: A higher deposit threshold will prioritize serious proposals that are backed by a substantial financial commitment, ensuring that governance resources are dedicated to addressing critical issues and improvements.


## Specification:
The proposed changes to the minimum deposit threshold for governance proposals are as follows:
- **Current Minimum Deposit**: 2,000 QSR tokens
- **Proposed Minimum Deposit**: 20,000 QSR tokens

## Voting
- By voting **YES**, you agree to the changes above proposal suggests.
- By voting **NO**, you disagree to the changes above proposal suggests.
- By voting **ABSTAIN**, you express no opinion on the matter.

detail.title: Decentralized Debit Card for Spending Quasar Tokens
detail.description:
Introduction
------------

We propose the development of a decentralized debit card that allows users to spend their Quasar tokens (QSR) at any coffee shops, grocery stores, or any other retailer worldwide. This innovative solution will provide our community with more flexibility and convenience when using their QSR tokens.


The Solution
-----------

To address this need, we plan to develop a decentralized debit card that integrates seamlessly with the Quasar wallet. This card will allow users to spend their QSR tokens at any point-of-sale (POS) terminal, online retailer, or ATM that accepts the most important debit cards.

Key Features
------------

1. Contactless Payments: Users can add the debit card to their mobile devices and make contactless payments using their Quasar tokens.
2. International Acceptance: The debit card can be used at any merchant that accepts payments worldwide.
3. Easy Integration: The card will be integrated with the Quasar wallet, allowing users to easily manage their QSR tokens and track their spending.
4. Security: The debit card will utilize advanced security measures, such as encryption, to protect users' assets.

Requirements
------------

To initiate the development of the decentralized debit card, we require 5 million Quasar tokens (QSR). These tokens will be used to cover the development costs and ensure the success of the project.

Timeline
--------

The development of the decentralized debit card is expected to take between 20-25 business days, depending on the complexity of the integration and testing processes. Once the card is developed, we will conduct thorough testing to ensure its stability and security before releasing it to the public.

Benefits
--------

The decentralized debit card will offer numerous benefits to our community, including:

1. Increased Flexibility: Users can spend their QSR tokens at any merchant that accepts payments, providing greater flexibility and convenience.
2. Accessibility: The debit card can be added to mobile devices, making it easy to use and manage QSR tokens on-the-go.
3. Security: The card will utilize advanced security measures to protect users' assets and prevent fraudulent activities.

Conclusion
----------

We believe that the development of a decentralized debit card for spending Quasar tokens (QSR) will greatly benefit our community by providing increased flexibility, accessibility, and security. We require 5 million QSR to initiate the development process and expect the card to be ready within 20-25 business days.

Please support this proposal by voting for it on our platform. Together, we can make the Quasar ecosystem even more robust and user-friendly.

detail.description:
# [Signaling Proposal]: Re-enabling QSR Incentives in OSMO PRO Vault
Authors: [Quasar](https://twitter.com/quasarfi)

# Summary
We propose the re-enabling of QSR incentives for the OSMO PRO, Quasar's first vault, which has been running successfully for over five months. To date, the vault has attracted 1.9M OSMO, almost reaching its deposit cap. Over 1.3M QSR tokens have been distributed to early vault depositors thus far, and we are now seeking to reintroduce these incentives to synchronize its ending with the ATOM PRO vault. 

## Specifications
Incentive Amount: 69,160 QSR
Duration: From passing the proposal up until block 2,705,000 (16th September 2023)

detail.title: [Chain upgrade] Proposal to add new modules
detail.description:
# [Chain upgrade] Proposal to add new modules
Authors: [Quasar](https://twitter.com/quasarfi)

# Summary
Dear Quasar Community,
The Quasar team is proposing a software upgrade (version v1) to introduce three new modules: qVesting, Token Factory, and Authz to the Quasar chain, aiming to enhance our chain's functionality and cater to evolving use cases in the Quasar chain.

Link to the [commonwealth forum proposal](https://gov.quasar.fi/discussion/12582-chain-upgrade-proposal-to-add-new-modules)

## Specifications
New on-chain modules include:

- qVesting Module:
    Introduces creation of continuous vesting accounts in the running chain with cliff periods, allowing gradual release of locked assets.  The existing vesting methods in the cosmos-sdk 0.45.x do not support creating a continuous vesting account with cliff period by specifying start time on the running chain.
- Token Factory Module:
    Enables native denom creation on the Quasar chain. Empowers projects to issue customizable tokens, fostering a diverse and dynamic token economy using smart contracts.
- Authz Module Integration:
    Enhances security and permission management. Provides granular control over user actions, enabling secure decentralized applications. The Authz module offers a flexible and efficient authorization system, granting developers greater control over user permissions and actions on the network.

## Benefits of the Upgrade
Improved token economic model for custom on-chain smart contracts.
Increased adoption and community empowerment.

## Halborn Audit
To further enhance the security and reliability of this upgrade, we have engaged the acclaimed blockchain security firm, Halborn, to conduct a comprehensive audit of the v1 software. This additional layer of scrutiny ensures that we are adhering to best practices and identifying potential vulnerabilities before the upgrade is deployed.
 
## Community Input
We recognize that our community's input and feedback are vital to the success of this upgrade. We encourage all community members to participate in the surrounding discussion and provide relevant feedback actively.
 
This proposed Quasar v1 upgrade represents a significant step forward for Quasar. By integrating the qVesting, Token Factory, and Authz modules, we are confident that we will foster a more vibrant, secure, and inclusive ecosystem. We value your engagement and support in this journey. 

## Voting
- By voting **YES**, you agree to upgrade the chain to v1.
- By voting **NO**, you disagree to upgrade the chain to v1.
- By voting **ABSTAIN**, you express no opinion on the matter.
- A **NoWithVeto** vote indicates a proposal either (1) is deemed to be spam, i.e., irrelevant to Quasar, (2) disproportionately infringes on minority interests, or (3) violates or encourages violation of the rules of engagement as currently set out by Quasar governance

detail.title: Parameter change proposal : To enable QSR Inflation
detail.description:
# Parameter change proposal : To enable QSR Inflation
*Authors:* [Quasar Team](https://twitter.com/quasarfi)

Dear Quasar Community,
We propose adjusting the mint module inflation parameter on the Quasar chain to enable staking rewards. This aims to incentivize participation in staking and delegation for network consensus to further improve the security of the chain and foster growth and stability within the Quasar ecosystem.

## Objective: 

The proposed change aims to achieve the following goals:
* Encourage participation: By introducing staking rewards, users will have a greater incentive to actively participate in the Quasar Chain network through token staking while gaining voting power for decision-making.
* Promote network stability: More validators and delegators attracted by staking rewards will enhance the overall security and stability of the Quasar Chain, making it less susceptible to malicious attacks.
* Support ecosystem growth: Staking rewards will create a positive feedback loop, increasing demand for Quasar Chain tokens and contributing to the ecosystem's growth.

## Proposal Details:
* Initial inflation rate: We suggest setting the initial inflation rate to 0.045 (4.5%) for the first year. This rate strikes a balance between incentivizing participation and ensuring long-term ecosystem sustainability.
* Gradual reduction: After the first year, a gradual reduction in the inflation rate will be implemented over subsequent years. This approach encourages continued network participation while maintaining ecosystem stability. Further inflation rate adjustments based on tokenomics projections will be considered in the future for optimal network performance.

We welcome input from all Quasar community members. Your perspectives are essential in shaping this proposed change. Let us engage in an open and collaborative discussion to address the interests and concerns of all stakeholders.

In conclusion, this proposal seeks to introduce staking rewards and enhance the Quasar Chain ecosystem's participation, stability, and growth. The initial inflation rate of 4.5% in the first year will incentivize users to stake their tokens, creating a thriving and sustainable environment for all participants.

**Voting**
* By voting **YES**, you agree to enable QSR token infaltion.
* By voting **NO**, you disagree to enable QSR token infaltion.
* By voting **ABSTAIN**, you express no opinion on the matter.
* A **NoWithVeto** vote indicates a proposal either
    * Is deemed to be spam, i.e., irrelevant to Quasar,
    * Disproportionately infringes on minority interests, or
    * Violates or encourages violation of the rules of engagement as currently set out by Quasar governance.

detail.title: Signaling Proposal: To add external QSR incentives to QSR/OSMO pool (ID:1060) on Osmosis AMM
detail.description:
# Signaling Proposal: To add external QSR incentives to QSR/OSMO pool (ID:1060) on Osmosis AMM

## Summary
We present a proposal to execute a 90-day incentive program designed to boost the recently established QSR/OSMO pool (ID: 1060), using external QSR tokens supplied by the Quasar Labs Association. Our main goal is to facilitate the external QSR rewards to the pool, stimulating liquidity providers to contribute, fostering trading activity, and enhancing the growth of the QSR/OSMO trading pair.
Link to the commonwealth [forum](https://commonwealth.im/quasar-finance/discussion/12154-signaling-proposal-to-add-external-qsr-incentives-to-qsrosmo-pool-id1060-on-osmosis-amm) proposal.

## Incentive Program Specifications:
*  APY: Liquidity providers in the QSR/OSMO pool can expect a competitive 10% Annual Percentage Yield (APY) boost at 1M TVL.
* Duration: This program will span 90 days, giving participants sufficient time to offer liquidity and earn rewards.
* Incentive Distribution: Rewards will be dispensed daily, proportional to each participant's liquidity contribution to the QSR/OSMO pool, Incentives will be added to the 14-day unbonding period only.  
* Total Incentive Amount: 914600 QSR
* Funding: The Quasar association account will fund these rewards, further boosting the APY for liquidity providers.

## Anticipated Outcomes:
* Enhanced Liquidity: The incentivized QSR/OSMO pool is expected to attract more liquidity, which will improve trading opportunities and market depth.
* Community Development: This program is designed to encourage active participation and increase governance involvement in the Quasar ecosystem.

## Governance Vote:
We invite all Quasar community members to actively participate in this proposal. Your insights and contributions are invaluable in shaping the discussion. The approval of this incentive program for the QSR/OSMO pool (Pool ID 1060) rests on your support.
Thank you for your consideration and active participation.

## Voting
* By voting YES, you agree to incentivize the Quasar/Osmosis pool.
* By voting NO, you disagree to incentivize the Quasar/Osmosis pool.
* By voting ABSTAIN, you express no opinion on the matter.
* A NoWithVeto vote indicates a proposal either (1) is deemed to be spam, i.e., irrelevant to Quasar, (2) disproportionately infringes on minority interests, or (3) violates or encourages violation of the rules of engagement as currently set out by Quasar governance

detail.title: Rectifying the Wording Error in Governance Proposal One: Ensuring Clarity and Precision
detail.description:
# Rectifying the Wording Error in Governance Proposal One: Ensuring Clarity and Precision

## Summary
Governance Proposal one was a parameter change proposal that contained an error in the vote section of the proposal description. Although the mistake did not result in any complications, we would like to address and rectify this error transparently on the chain by providing the correct wording in this proposal.

## Background
The first Quasar governance proposal was launched on June 27th, 2023, as a parameter change proposal aimed at re-enabling QSR transactions. The proposal was successful in achieving its intended purpose. However, an error was identified in the proposal voting text description, which contained the following wording:

* By voting YES, you agree that the community pool tax rate should be changed to 10%.
* By voting NO, you disagree that the community pool tax rate should be changed to 10%.
* By voting ABSTAIN, you express no opinion on the matter.
* A NoWithVeto vote indicates a proposal either (1) is deemed to be spam, i.e., irrelevant to Quasar, (2) disproportionately infringes on minority interests, or (3) violates or encourages violation of the rules of engagement as currently set out by Quasar governance.

The above wording is incorrect as the proposal did not concern the community pool tax rate; rather, its focus was on enabling QSR transactions. The accurate and appropriate wording should have been as follows:

* By voting YES, you agree that the transfer of Quasar tokens (QSR) should be enabled again.
* By voting NO, you disagree that the transfer of Quasar tokens (QSR) should be enabled again.
* By voting ABSTAIN, you express no opinion on the matter.
* A NoWithVeto vote indicates a proposal either (1) is deemed to be spam, i.e., irrelevant to Quasar, (2) disproportionately infringes on minority interests, or (3) violates or encourages violation of the rules of engagement as currently set out by Quasar governance.

However, proposal one was successfully approved without direct impact from this mistake, as the implemented code conformed to the intended nature of the proposal's description and functioned effectively. Consequently, no adverse effects or complications arose from this mistake.

## Voting
* By voting YES, you agree to save this wording correction for governance proposal one on chain.
* By voting NO, you disagree with saving this wording correction for governance proposal one on chain.
* By voting ABSTAIN, you express no opinion on the matter.
* A NoWithVeto vote indicates a proposal either (1) is deemed to be spam, i.e., irrelevant to Quasar, (2) disproportionately infringes on minority interests, or (3) violates or encourages violation of the rules of engagement as currently set out by Quasar governance

detail.description:
# Parameter Change: Increase of active Validator Set
*Authors:* [Quasar Team](https://twitter.com/quasarfi)

## Summary
Currently, the max validator set size of the Quasar blockchain is 35 validators. The aim of this proposal is to increase the size of the max validator set from 35 to 50 validators.

## Background
The Quasar blockchain is currently validated by 26 selected validators at the time of this proposal. With the QSR token launch coming up next week, we are taking another major step towards the decentralization of the Quasar blockchain. This is relevant in preparation for enabling inflation and staking rewards since having a bigger validator set supports greater decentralization and strengthens the protocol for increased community participation and validation.

**Voting**
* By voting **YES**, you agree to expanding the active validator set to 50.
* By voting **NO**, you disagree with expanding the active validator set to 50.
* By voting **ABSTAIN**, you express no opinion on the matter.

detail.title: Parameter Change: Enable transfer of Quasar tokens
detail.description:
# Parameter Change : Enable transfer of Quasar tokens 
*Authors:* [Quasar Team](https://twitter.com/quasarfi) 

## Summary 
The aim of this proposal is to enable the transfer of Quasar tokens (QSR) which has been disabled since the mainnet launch. Doing so will allow the release of QSR to the public, meaning Quasar can function more permissionless and securely, and that planned features such as a protocol-owned liquidity mechanism become possible. 

## Background 
The functions of QSR, as outlined in the Quasar litepaper, are: 
* Driving PoS consensus (including transaction fee payment)
* On-chain governance
* Treasury governance
* Vault creation

Currently, validators are the only holders of QSR. Transfers of QSR have been disabled since mainnet launch to ensure a more stable environment for the release and further development of vaults on the Quasar web app. Transaction fees have been paid in OSMO to allow vaults to operate without requiring users to hold QSR.

Quasar is now ready for the public release of the QSR token. This will set the stage for greater community participation by opening the network to wider governance in all elements of PoS consensus including delegation, validation, and voting in future chain proposals. Planned features like permissionless vault creation and protocol-owned liquidity via a community treasury would also facilitate Quasar’s community and require the free flow of QSR.


## What are the next steps after enabling token transfer? 
Enabling transfers of QSR unlocks the ability to carry out a release of QSR to the public and our community. This will be done via StreamSwap, an Osmosis-based protocol for time-based token transfers. StreamSwap allows for transparent price discovery and efficient liquidity bootstrapping. More details on StreamSwap can be found [here](https://mirror.xyz/streamswapprotocol.eth/3-x3fWlrkoLfwM7lOTxDL1lboWJp9u3RzszHUHc0BPM).

**Voting:** 
* By voting **YES**, you agree that the community pool tax rate should be changed to 10%. 
* By voting **NO**, you disagree that the community pool tax rate should be changed to 10%. 
* By voting **ABSTAIN**, you express no opinion on the matter. 
* A **NoWithVeto** vote indicates a proposal either (1) is deemed to be spam, i.e., irrelevant to Quasar, (2) disproportionately infringes on minority interests, or (3) violates or encourages violation of the rules of engagement as currently set out by Quasar governance.
